\[\frac{1}{2} \pi r^2 + \frac{1}{2} \pi s^2 - \frac{1}{2} r^2 \arccos \left( \frac{h}{r} \right) - \frac{1}{2} s^2 \arccos \left( \frac{r + s - h}{s} \right).\]Since the area of the shaded region is half the total area, we have
\[\frac{1}{2} \pi r^2 + \frac{1}{2} \pi s^2 - \frac{1}{2} r^2 \arccos \left( \frac{h}{r} \right) - \frac{1}{2} s^2 \arccos \left( \frac{r + s - h}{s} \right) = \frac{1}{2} \pi (r + s)^2.\]Then
\[\pi r^2 + \pi s^2 - r^2 \arccos \left( \frac{h}{r} \right) - s^2 \arccos \left( \frac{r + s - h}{s} \right) = \pi (r + s)^2.\]This simplifies to
\[\arccos \left( \frac{h}{r} \right) + \arccos \left( \frac{r + s - h}{s} \right) = \pi.\]By the Law of Cosines on triangle $ACP,$
\[\cos \angle ACP = \frac{r^2 + h^2 - (r + s)^2}{2rh} = \frac{h^2 - 2rh - s^2}{2rh}.\]By the Law of Cosines on triangle $BCP,$
\[\cos \angle BCP = \frac{s^2 + (r + s - h)^2 - r^2}{2s(r + s - h)} = \frac{h^2 - 2rh - r^2}{2sh}.\]Then
\begin{align*}
\cos \angle ACP + \cos \angle BCP &= \frac{h^2 - 2rh - s^2}{2rh} + \frac{h^2 - 2rh - r^2}{2sh} \\
&= \frac{h^3 - (r + s)h^2 + r^2 s + rs^2}{2rsh}.
\end{align*}Hence, $\cos \angle ACP + \cos \angle BCP = 0,$ so
\[\cos \angle ACP = -\cos \angle BCP.\]Then $\angle ACP$ and $\angle BCP$ are supplementary, which means $\angle ACP = 180^\circ - \angle BCP.$  Therefore,
\[\angle ACP = \frac{180^\circ - \arccos \left( \frac{h^2 - 2rh - r^2}{2sh} \right)}{\pi} \cdot 180^\circ = \boxed{39.2^\circ}.\]

